result.execSummary:
The defendant Dangelo Ray Kingsby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dangelo Ray Kingsby in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Defendant Dangelo Ray Kingsby in custody.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Parties have reached a resolution and proceed with plea and sentencing.  
As to Counts 1 and 2:    Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    
As to Counts 1 and 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 4 months in the House of Correction, concurrent to each other, with credit of 37 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation with the Mental Health Unit for 12 months with the following conditions:
*No new violations that rise to the level of probable cause.
*Maintain absolute sobriety. 
*Defendant to pay all costs and surcharges, as to each count, during period of probation.  If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.
Appeal rights given.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.
Court ordered defendant to be monitored by Drug Testing
Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant advised No Contact Order remains in full force and effect.  
Defendant to have no contact with:All Walmart Stores located in Milwaukee County, State of Wisconsin.
